

The shares prices in Singapore closed sharply higher on Tuesday with the benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) rising 31.5 points to end at 2802.9 points.

The overall volume stood at 1.3292 billion shares worth 1.2262 billion Singapore dollars (about 788.5 million U.S. dollars).

Gainers led losers by 380 to 227 with another 730 unchanged.

On Monday, the STI fell 41.8 points to end at 2771.4 points.

